    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-6k5MZXGZfN0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAhc/UZLHbUbp_a0/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 512127,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4111488,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4111488/aashi-kwatra",
                "reputation": 29,
                "display_name": "aashi Kwatra"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1412544668,
            "creation_date": 1412544668,
            "body": "<p>Adding following line in eclipse.ini worked for me<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>-vm\n/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.6/Commands/java\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 26207435,
            "question_id": 25196078
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2d5c15764ccbbe7693103592009f6117?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1639650,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1512358,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1512358/sid-sarasvati",
                "reputation": 855,
                "display_name": "Sid Sarasvati"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1418178939,
            "creation_date": 1416118644,
            "body": "<p>ADT bundle does not work with the Oracle Java 7 SE JDK, failing with an NPE in the Android Application Project wizard.<\/p>\n\n<p>Here's a workaround that lets you keep Java 7 as the default but run ADT with Java 6 when you have both installed. Bring up $ADT_DIR/eclipse/Eclipse.app/Contents/MacOS/eclipse.ini in an editor.  Before the -vmargs line, insert these two lines:<\/p>\n\n<p><div class=\"snippet\" data-lang=\"js\" data-hide=\"false\">\r\n<div class=\"snippet-code\">\r\n<pre class=\"snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override\"><code>-vm\r\n/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.6/Commands/java<\/code><\/pre>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 26954440,
            "question_id": 25196078,
            "last_edit_date": 1418178939
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/DaJ7l.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 226762,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2162226,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2162226/gene-bo",
                "reputation": 12231,
                "display_name": "Gene Bo",
                "accept_rate": 70
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1423763477,
            "creation_date": 1423718440,
            "body": "<p>After struggling with this issue for a while, it was a combination of answers that solved it for me:<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Needed to update eclipse.ini as mentioned above: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/26207435/2162226\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/26207435/2162226<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>-vm\n    /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_80.jdk/Contents/Home\n    -vmargs<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p>In AndroidManifest.xml set minSdk='14'\nAs mentioned here: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/22564119/2162226\">https://stackoverflow.com/a/22564119/2162226<\/a>\nWhen creating a new project \"the folder appcompat_v7 doesnt get created\" with minSdk=14<\/p><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
            "answer_id": 28469889,
            "question_id": 25196078,
            "last_edit_date": 1495541559
        }
    ],
